00:42:23.170 --> 00:42:25.480
So what have we found?

00:42:25.480 --> 00:42:31.820
We have found that as
this fluid is moving

00:42:31.820 --> 00:42:35.240
at some finite
temperature T, it will

00:42:35.240 --> 00:42:38.220
generate these excitations.

00:42:38.220 --> 00:42:41.200
And these excitations
are preferably

00:42:41.200 --> 00:42:44.520
