00:43:24.040 --> 00:43:28.710
I have a density of
these excitations.

00:43:28.710 --> 00:43:31.480
And what we have established
is that the density

00:43:31.480 --> 00:43:35.000
of those excitations
is proportional to t

00:43:35.000 --> 00:43:36.430
to the fourth.

00:43:36.430 --> 00:43:40.190
And what is happening in this
Andronikashvili experiment

00:43:40.190 --> 00:43:45.170
is that as these plates are
moving, by this mechanism

00:43:45.170 --> 00:43:47.230
the superfluid
that is in contact

00:43:47.230 --> 00:43:50.740
with them will
create excitations.

00:43:50.740 --> 00:43:53.720
And the momentum of
those excitations

00:43:53.720 --> 00:43:57.130
would correspond to some
kind of a density that

00:43:57.130 --> 00:44:00.540
vanishes as T to
the fourth, again

00:44:00.540 --> 00:44:06.370
