00:50:11.418 --> 00:50:15.402
liquid phases-- a
warmer and a colder one.

00:50:15.402 --> 00:50:19.137
The warmer phase is called
liquid helium I and the colder

00:50:19.137 --> 00:50:21.876
phase liquid helium II.

00:50:21.876 --> 00:50:25.860
The two stages are separated
by a transition temperature,

00:50:25.860 --> 00:50:28.570
known as the lambda point.

00:50:28.570 --> 00:50:31.725
When liquid helium is pulled
down through the lambda point,

00:50:31.725 --> 00:50:36.610
